{"questionId":"5684","questionHtml":"<p>Identify the type of chemical reaction that occurs between fatty acids and glycerol to&nbsp;form lipids and the by-product of the reaction.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/1edeff95056006f441e5314c28c958333afda00d.png\"></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em>Type of reaction:</em></p>\n<p>condensation</p>\n<p><strong><em>OR</em></strong></p>\n<p>esterification/triesterification</p>\n<p><strong><em>OR</em></strong></p>\n<p>nucleophilic substitution/nucleophilic displacement/S<sub>N</sub>2</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>By-product:</em></p>\n<p>water/H<sub>2</sub>O</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Do </em><strong><em>not </em></strong><em>accept just&nbsp;</em><em>“substitution/displacement”.</em></p>\n<p><strong><em>[2 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"5684","referenceCode":"18M.3.sl.TZ2.6a","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Identify the type of chemical reaction that occurs between fatty acids and glycerol to form lipids and the by-product of the reaction.","paper":"3","level":"sl","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Options","Options","B: Biochemistry","B.1 Introduction to biochemistry","Options","B: Biochemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}